Protocol reference

The goJTOpen wire-format implementation was written using the
open-source IBM Toolbox for Java (JTOpen) as a reference for the IBM i
host-server datastream protocol. JTOpen is © International Business
Machines Corporation and others, and is licensed under the IBM Public
License v1.0 (https://opensource.org/license/ibm-pl-1-0).

goJTOpen is a clean-room reimplementation in Go. No JTOpen source
code is included in this repository or copied at build time. The
Java fixture-capture harness under testdata/jtopen-fixtures/ depends
on JTOpen at runtime via Maven Central to record wire traces; the
captured fixtures themselves are byte data, not derivative works of
JTOpen source.
